"title": "5083: Adam, and Jesus Christ",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "5083",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>Paul presents Jesus Christ as both the last Adam, succeeding where the first Adam failed, and the second man, standing at the head of a new humanity.</p>\n<h2>The contrast between the first and second Adam</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom5:14\">ROM 5:14</a></strong> <em>By his sin Adam brought universal misery on humanity. In this he is the foreshadower and prototype of Jesus Christ, who through his righteous act brings the universal hope of redemption.</em></p>\n<h2>The contrast in nature of the first Adam and the second Adam</h2>\n<h3>Adam was a living being; Jesus Christ is a life-giving being</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor15:45\">1CO 15:45</a></strong></p>\n<h3>Adam was natural, Jesus Christ is spiritual</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor15:46\">1CO 15:46</a></strong></p>\n<h3>Adam was earthly, Jesus Christ is heavenly</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor15:47\">1CO 15:47</a></strong></p>\n<h2>The contrast in the consequences of the actions of the first Adam and the second Adam</h2>\n<h3>Adam brought death, Jesus Christ brings life</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom5:15\">ROM 5:15</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom5:17\">ROM 5:17</a></strong>; <strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor15:21-1Cor15:23\">1CO 15:21–15:23</a></strong></p>\n<h3>Adam brought judgment, Jesus Christ brings justification</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom5:16\">ROM 5:16</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom5:18-Rom5:19\">ROM 5:18–5:19</a></strong></p>\n<h3>The assurance this doctrine brings</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor15:48-1Cor15:49\">1CO 15:48–15:49</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Phil3:20-Phil3:21\">PHP 3:20–3:21</a></p>",
